  "text": "The HTTP filter chain registration and execution in Envoy follows a multi-stage pipeline:\n\n**1. Configuration and Registration (Compile-Time):**\n- The HttpConnectionManager protobuf message (api/envoy/extensions/filters/network/http_connection_manager/v3/http_connection_manager.proto) defines the `http_filters` field as a repeated HttpFilter array. Each HttpFilter message contains: `name` (filter config name), `config_type` (typed_config or config_discovery for dynamic filters), `is_optional`, and `disabled` fields.\n- HttpConnectionManagerFilterConfigFactory reads this protobuf config and creates an HttpConnectionManagerConfig instance, which implements the FilterChainFactory interface.\n- During HttpConnectionManagerConfig construction (source/extensions/filters/network/http_connection_manager/config.cc, line 709-715), a FilterChainHelper template class is instantiated to process the http_filters field.\n- FilterChainHelper::processFilters() method iterates through each HttpFilter and calls processFilter() to create filter factories. Each filter factory is retrieved from the registry using Config::Utility::getAndCheckFactory() and is wrapped in a FilterConfigProvider.\n- These filter factories are stored in HttpConnectionManagerConfig::filter_factories_ as a list of FilterFactoryProvider objects containing both the factory callback and a disabled flag.\n\n**2. Stream Creation and Filter Chain Construction (Runtime):**\n- When a new HTTP stream is created on the connection, the connection manager calls HttpConnectionManagerConfig::createFilterChain() (the FilterChainFactory interface method).\n- This method delegates to FilterChainUtility::createFilterChainForFactories() (source/common/http/filter_chain_helper.cc), passing the filter_factories_ list and a FilterChainManager interface pointer.\n- FilterChainUtility::createFilterChainForFactories() iterates through each filter factory in the list, checking if the filter is disabled via FilterChainOptions::filterDisabled(). If not disabled, it retrieves the filter factory callback and calls FilterChainManager::applyFilterFactoryCb() with the factory context and callback.\n\n**3. Filter Instantiation and Chain Execution (Runtime):**\n- The FilterChainManager is implemented by FilterManager (source/common/http/filter_manager.h), which provides a FilterChainFactoryCallbacksImpl inner class that implements the FilterChainFactoryCallbacks interface (envoy/http/filter.h, lines 1224-1257).\n- When a factory callback is invoked, it receives a FilterChainFactoryCallbacks instance. The factory creates the actual filter instance and calls one of: addStreamDecoderFilter(), addStreamEncoderFilter(), or addStreamFilter().\n- FilterChainFactoryCallbacksImpl::addStreamDecoderFilter() (source/common/http/filter_manager.h, lines 918-922) wraps the filter in an ActiveStreamDecoderFilter and adds it to FilterManager's decoder filter list.\n- Similarly, addStreamEncoderFilter() adds to the encoder filter list, and addStreamFilter() adds to both.\n- At runtime, when stream events (headers, data, trailers, metadata) arrive, FilterManager::decodeHeaders(), decodeData(), decodeTrailers() iterate through the decoder filter chain sequentially, calling the corresponding filter methods.\n- Filter return codes (FilterHeadersStatus, FilterDataStatus, etc.) control whether iteration continues or stops. When a filter stops iteration, FilterManager buffers data and waits for the filter to call continueDecoding().\n- For response processing, the encoder filter chain is similarly iterated through encodeHeaders(), encodeData(), encodeTrailers() methods.\n- The execution continues through all filters in order until the final terminal filter (typically the router filter) generates a response, which then flows backward through the encoder filter chain.\n\n**Key Interfaces and Classes:**\n- FilterChainFactory (envoy/http/filter_factory.h): Abstract interface with createFilterChain() and createUpgradeFilterChain() methods implemented by HttpConnectionManagerConfig.\n- FilterChainManager (envoy/http/filter_factory.h): Sink interface that accepts filter factories via applyFilterFactoryCb(), implemented by FilterManager.\n- FilterChainFactoryCallbacks (envoy/http/filter.h): Provides addStreamDecoderFilter(), addStreamEncoderFilter(), addStreamFilter() methods for factories to instantiate and register filters.\n- FilterChainHelper<FilterCtx, NamedHttpFilterFactory> (source/common/http/filter_chain_helper.h): Template class that processes protobuf filter configurations and creates factory callbacks using registry lookup.\n- FilterChainUtility (source/common/http/filter_chain_helper.h): Static utility that creates filter chains from pre-constructed filter factories, applying them to a FilterChainManager.\n- FilterManager (source/common/http/filter_manager.h): Core runtime filter execution engine that maintains decoder/encoder filter lists and iterates them sequentially for each stream event.\n- HttpConnectionManagerConfig (source/extensions/filters/network/http_connection_manager/config.h): Implements FilterChainFactory, caches parsed filter_factories_ from protobuf config, and creates filter chains on demand for new streams."
}

